Web APIs


    - Apis offered in client-side JavaScript

    - Generally, these fall into two categories
        1) Browser Apis
            - built into your web browser
            - expose data and functionality available within your web browser
            - available to you from the start, provided you are writing in a browser


            Common Browser Apis and Uses

                Document Manipulation
                    - think the DOM
                
                APIs for fetching data from a server
                    - XMLHttpRequest
                    - fetch Api
                    - axios
                
                APIs for drawing and manipulating graphics
                    - canvas
                    - webgl
                
                Audio and Video Apis
                    - HTMLMediaElement
                    - Web Audio API
                    - Web RTC           : Real Time Communication

                Device APIs
                    - Notification API
                    - Vibration API 

                Client-side storage APIs
                    - Web Storage API
                        - local & session storage
                    - IndexedDB API



        2) Third-Party Apis
            - these are separate Apis provided by some outside source
            - ex. Twitter API 
    

            Common Third-Party APIs
                
                Twitter API
                
                Map APIs
                    - Mapquest
                    - Google Maps API
                
                Facebook APIs
                
                Telegram APIs
                
                Youtube API

                Pinterest API

                Twilio API

                Mastodon API
